# Services that need a sibling directory their own folder can't reach build
# with a repo-root context instead of their own directory: the Go services
# (tenancy-service, claims-gateway, registry-service, provisioner — sibling
# Go modules auth-contracts/auth-middleware), twin-service and agent-service
# (server/auth-policy + server/auth-contracts, read via relative path/
# include_str! for local Cedar authorization). Everything else still builds
# with its own directory as context and never sees this file. Keep this list
# tight: it's the difference between a multi-GB and a multi-MB build context
# for those Dockerfiles.
.git
node_modules
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/target
**/coverage
client
landing-page
documentation
simulators
k8s
**/*.md
